Paramedics are  at the scene  where a house  collapsed in Bonela in  Cato Manor in Durban and in which a mother and her two daughters are reported to be trapped under rubble. ALS Paramedics spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said a sand bank collapsed at the rear of the house, causing the structural collapse. “Fortunately, the father managed to escape but the mother and two daughters are missing. The team is waiting for search and rescue to  assist.” Dozens of roads in Durban have been closed, leaving motorists stranded as they head to school and work. Traffic authorities reported the following roads were affected: In the north: In the west: This is a developing story. TimesLIVE 